INSERT INTO `lesson_question` (`id`, `created_at`, `status`, `updated_at`, `content`, `explanation`) VALUES (1,'2025-05-17 09:26:42.131676',_binary '','2025-05-17 09:26:42.131690','What does the word \"pollution\" mean?','Pollution refers to the introduction of harmful materials into the environment, such as smoke, chemicals, or plastic, that cause damage to air, water, or land.'),(2,'2025-05-17 09:27:12.454890',_binary '','2025-05-17 09:27:12.454899','What is \"deforestation\"?','Deforestation means removing trees from forests on a large scale, often for farming or construction, which negatively impacts the environment and wildlife.'),(3,'2025-05-17 09:27:40.947095',_binary '','2025-05-17 09:27:40.947104','Which of the following is an example of recycling?','Recycling involves processing used materials (like bottles or cans) so they can be used again, reducing waste and saving resources.'),(4,'2025-05-17 09:28:09.856554',_binary '','2025-05-17 09:28:09.856566','What does the word \"sustainable\" refer to?','Sustainable practices are those that meet current needs without harming future generations or the planet, such as using renewable energy or reducing waste.'),(5,'2025-05-17 09:28:36.708584',_binary '','2025-05-17 09:28:36.708592','What is a greenhouse effect?','The greenhouse effect happens when gases like CO₂ trap heat in the Earth\'s atmosphere, leading to an increase in global temperatures.'),(6,'2025-05-17 09:29:05.075906',_binary '','2025-05-17 09:29:05.075915','What is climate change mostly caused by?','Climate change is largely caused by human actions such as burning coal, oil, and gas, which release greenhouse gases and affect global climate patterns.'),(7,'2025-05-17 09:38:09.865470',_binary '','2025-05-17 09:38:09.865489','Which sentence is in the correct simple present form?','In the simple present tense, we add -es to the verb when the subject is he/she/it. → \"goes\"'),(8,'2025-05-17 09:38:35.903816',_binary '','2025-05-17 09:38:35.903825','What is the negative form of: “He eats vegetables”?','In the negative form, use “doesn’t + base verb”. No -s after the verb.'),(9,'2025-05-17 09:39:04.494281',_binary '','2025-05-17 09:39:04.494291','Which question is correct in the simple present tense?','Use “Does + subject + base verb” for yes/no questions. Never add -s to the main verb in a question.'),(10,'2025-05-17 09:39:31.457638',_binary '','2025-05-17 09:39:31.457648','What time expression is commonly used with the simple present tense?','\"Every morning\" refers to a regular action, which is typical for the simple present.'),(11,'2025-05-17 09:39:58.224039',_binary '','2025-05-17 09:39:58.224056','Which of the following shows a habit?','Habits are described using the simple present with time expressions like \"every morning\".'),(12,'2025-05-17 09:48:24.305560',_binary '','2025-05-17 09:48:24.305587','Where does Anna go on Sunday?','The passage states that Anna goes to the park on Sunday.'),(13,'2025-05-17 09:49:04.636402',_binary '','2025-05-17 09:49:04.636412','What does Anna bring to the park?','Anna brings a book and a sandwich to the park, as mentioned in the passage.'),(14,'2025-05-17 10:18:36.828268',_binary '','2025-05-17 10:18:36.828290','What does Emma want to cook with the vegetables she is buying?',' In the conversation, Emma asks the vendor \"And what would you recommend for a stir-fry?\" '),(15,'2025-06-01 16:27:02.385928',_binary '','2025-06-01 16:27:02.385939','What do you call a piece of furniture used for sitting?','This question asks for the name of a common household item where people sit.'),(16,'2025-06-01 16:27:27.719711',_binary '','2025-06-01 16:27:27.719722','Which item is used to store food at a low temperature?','The correct answer is the appliance that keeps food cold.'),(17,'2025-06-01 16:27:54.952670',_binary '','2025-06-01 16:27:54.952678','Where would you look to see your reflection?','This item shows your image when you look at it.'),(18,'2025-06-01 16:28:20.527876',_binary '','2025-06-01 16:28:20.527885','What is a long, comfortable seat for multiple people called?','This piece of furniture is usually found in living rooms.'),(19,'2025-06-01 16:28:53.162080',_binary '','2025-06-01 16:28:53.162106','Which item provides light in a dark room?','The correct answer is an object that produces light.'),(20,'2025-06-01 16:54:42.789686',_binary '','2025-06-01 16:54:42.789696','Which verb means \"to share information or ideas with others\"?','This action involves exchanging messages.'),(21,'2025-06-01 16:55:08.702328',_binary '','2025-06-01 16:55:08.702337','What is the opposite of speaking loudly?','This verb describes speaking very softly.'),(22,'2025-06-01 16:55:36.790050',_binary '','2025-06-01 16:55:36.790059','Which adjective describes someone who is respectful and considerate?','This word describes good manners.'),(23,'2025-06-01 16:56:07.116443',_binary '','2025-06-01 16:56:07.116452','What adverb means \"in a way that is easy to understand\"?','This describes speaking without confusion.'),(24,'2025-06-01 16:56:32.720768',_binary '','2025-06-01 16:56:32.720778','Which word means \"to convince someone to do something\"?',' This verb involves changing someone’s opinion.'),(25,'2025-06-01 18:10:43.740053',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:10:43.740066','What is the purpose of a salutation in a letter?','It introduces the recipient at the beginning.'),(26,'2025-06-01 18:11:06.577852',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:11:06.577862','Which word means \"to add a file to an email\"?','This action includes supplementary documents.'),(27,'2025-06-01 18:11:31.251597',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:11:31.251608','How should a job application email be written?','It requires professional language.'),(28,'2025-06-01 18:11:59.730796',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:11:59.730807','Which adverb is commonly used in letter closings?','It expresses genuine feelings.'),(29,'2025-06-01 18:12:26.209779',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:12:26.209792','What should you include to identify the email\'s content quickly?','It summarizes the email’s purpose.'),(30,'2025-06-01 18:32:28.728160',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:32:28.728172','Which sentence is correct?','The correct answer is B because, in the Present Simple tense, for he/she/it, we add -s/-es to the verb. \"Go\" becomes \"goes\" for the third-person singular.'),(31,'2025-06-01 18:33:01.206210',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:33:01.206219','What is the negative form of \"They play football\"?','The correct answer is C because, in negative Present Simple sentences, we use \"do not\" (don’t) or \"does not\" (doesn’t) before the base verb. Since \"they\" is plural, we use \"don’t.\"'),(32,'2025-06-01 18:33:33.303139',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:33:33.303150','Which sentence describes a general truth?','The correct answer is B because general truths (facts that are always true) use the Present Simple tense. \"Cats drink milk\" is a general fact, while the other options describe temporary actions or past events.'),(33,'2025-06-01 18:34:07.094227',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:34:07.094240','Choose the correct question form:','The correct answer is B because, in Present Simple questions with he/she/it, we use \"Does\" + base verb (like). \"Do he likes\" is incorrect because \"does\" already indicates the third person, so the verb should remain in its base form.'),(34,'2025-06-01 18:34:44.239510',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:34:44.239520','Which sentence is incorrect?','The correct answer is B because \"studies\" is incorrect for the subject \"we.\" The correct form should be \"study\" since plural subjects (we/you/they) do not take -s/-es in the Present Simple.'),(35,'2025-06-01 18:39:18.010467',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:39:18.010479','Which sentence is correct in the Present Continuous Tense?','The Present Continuous requires \"am/is/are + verb-ing.\" Only option B follows this rule.'),(36,'2025-06-01 18:39:51.908162',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:39:51.908183','What is the correct form of the verb in this sentence?\n\n\"They ___________ football in the park.\"','The subject \"They\" requires \"are + verb-ing.\"'),(37,'2025-06-01 18:40:28.523697',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:40:28.523717','Which time expression is NOT commonly used with Present Continuous?','\"Yesterday\" refers to the past, while Present Continuous describes current actions.'),(38,'2025-06-01 18:40:59.813586',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:40:59.813596','Choose the sentence that describes a future plan.','Present Continuous can describe future plans when a time reference (e.g., \"tonight\") is given.'),(39,'2025-06-01 18:41:32.475494',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:41:32.475503','Which sentence is INCORRECT in Present Continuous?','Verbs like \"like,\" \"love,\" \"know,\" and \"believe\" are stative and rarely used in continuous forms.'),(40,'2025-06-01 18:48:00.018857',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:48:00.018880','Which sentence is correct in the Simple Future Tense?','The Simple Future requires \"will + base verb\" or \"be going to + base verb.\"'),(41,'2025-06-01 18:48:47.662464',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:48:47.662474','What is the correct form of the verb in this sentence?\nWe ___________ a movie tonight.','The Simple Future uses \"will\" or \"be going to\" before the base verb.'),(42,'2025-06-01 18:49:07.275377',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:49:07.275394','Which time expression is NOT commonly used with Simple Future?','Simple Future refers to later events, not past or habitual actions.'),(43,'2025-06-01 18:49:36.597085',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:49:36.597097','Choose the sentence that describes a spontaneous decision.','\"Will\" is often used for quick decisions made at the moment.'),(44,'2025-06-01 18:50:00.527821',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:50:00.527826','Which sentence is INCORRECT in Simple Future?','\"Will\" should be followed by a base verb, not past tense.'),(45,'2025-06-01 18:54:52.052280',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:54:52.052300','Which sentence is correct in the Simple Past Tense?','The Simple Past describes completed actions, often with past time expressions.'),(46,'2025-06-01 18:55:16.856941',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:55:16.856952','What is the correct past form of the verb in this sentence? She ___________ her homework before dinner.','Regular verbs add \"-ed\"; irregular verbs have unique past forms.'),(47,'2025-06-01 18:55:39.158467',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:55:39.158472','Which time expression is NOT used with the Simple Past?','Simple Past refers to finished actions, not present or future times.'),(48,'2025-06-01 18:56:00.504870',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:56:00.504875','Choose the sentence that uses an irregular past tense verb correctly.','Irregular verbs (e.g., \"write → wrote\") don’t follow the \"-ed\" rule.'),(49,'2025-06-01 18:56:24.609765',_binary '','2025-06-01 18:56:24.609771','Which sentence is INCORRECT in the Simple Past?','The past form must match the verb type (regular/irregular).'),(50,'2025-06-01 19:24:21.966915',_binary '','2025-06-01 19:24:21.966924','Which sentence correctly uses Present Perfect?','This tense connects past actions to the present moment.'),(51,'2025-06-01 19:24:45.812917',_binary '','2025-06-01 19:24:45.812923','What is the correct form of the verb? He ___________ that book three times.','Present Perfect uses \"have/has\" + past participle.'),(52,'2025-06-01 19:25:09.509097',_binary '','2025-06-01 19:25:09.509105','Which time expression is NOT used with Present Perfect?','Present Perfect doesn\'t use specific past time references.'),(53,'2025-06-01 19:25:38.857171',_binary '','2025-06-01 19:25:38.857185','Choose the sentence showing a continuing action from past to present.','\"Since\" indicates an action that started in the past and continues.'),(54,'2025-06-01 19:31:45.181894',_binary '','2025-06-01 19:31:45.181912','Which sentence is INCORRECT in Present Perfect?','The past participle form must be used correctly.'),(55,'2025-06-01 21:44:18.677938',_binary '','2025-06-01 21:44:18.677980','Why does Emma ask Jack to put his bottle in the recycling bin?','Emma mentions that littering harms animals, emphasizing environmental responsibility.'),(56,'2025-06-01 21:44:46.218511',_binary '','2025-06-01 21:44:46.218534','What does Lisa think about Emma’s volunteer work?','Lisa says, \"More people should do this!\" showing support.'),(57,'2025-06-01 21:45:14.826276',_binary '','2025-06-01 21:45:14.826296','How often does Emma’s group organize clean-up events?','Emma states, \"We organize clean-up events every month.\"'),(58,'2025-06-01 21:45:45.021201',_binary '','2025-06-01 21:45:45.021232','What is one problem caused by plastic waste in the park?','Emma explains that plastic waste \"can hurt wildlife.\"'),(59,'2025-06-01 21:46:17.141699',_binary '','2025-06-01 21:46:17.141716','What does Lisa say she might do in the future?','Lisa says, \"Maybe I’ll join next time!\" showing interest in volunteering.'),(60,'2025-06-01 22:24:22.900356',_binary '','2025-06-01 22:24:22.900368','What is Jake’s main concern about the exam?','Jake mentions that he still needs to review the formulas, indicating he doesn’t feel fully prepared.'),(61,'2025-06-01 22:24:48.469253',_binary '','2025-06-01 22:24:48.469261','How does Emma feel about the exam?','Emma says she’s been practicing but is still nervous.'),(62,'2025-06-01 22:25:17.792335',_binary '','2025-06-01 22:25:17.792348','What do they decide to do before the exam?','They agree to meet early to review one more time.'),(63,'2025-06-01 22:25:44.419761',_binary '','2025-06-01 22:25:44.419770','What tool does Jake mention using during the exam?','Jake talks about using a calculator for complex calculations.'),(64,'2025-06-01 22:26:11.247708',_binary '','2025-06-01 22:26:11.247716','What emotion do both students share?','Both admit feeling nervous or anxious about the exam.'),(65,'2025-06-02 13:51:47.652342',_binary '','2025-06-02 13:51:47.652369','What is the maximum resolution supported by the new console?','The presenter specifically mentions \"true 8K resolution\" as a feature.'),(66,'2025-06-02 13:52:16.864423',_binary '','2025-06-02 13:52:16.864451','What improvement was made to the controller?','The presenter highlights \"advanced haptic feedback\" as a controller feature.'),(67,'2025-06-02 13:52:42.127187',_binary '','2025-06-02 13:52:42.127197','What does backward compatibility allow?','The presenter states older games will \"work seamlessly\" on the new system.'),(68,'2025-06-02 13:53:07.842235',_binary '','2025-06-02 13:53:07.842246','What eliminates loading screens?','The \"ultra-fast SSD storage\" is mentioned as solving loading times.'),(69,'2025-06-02 13:53:36.193313',_binary '','2025-06-02 13:53:36.193326','When do pre-orders begin?','The presenter clearly states \"Pre-orders start tomorrow.\"'),(70,'2025-06-02 14:47:01.707346',_binary '','2025-06-02 14:47:01.707351','What is the purpose of a harness in climbing?','The text states that a harness secures the climber to a rope, ensuring safety.'),(71,'2025-06-02 14:47:25.834481',_binary '','2025-06-02 14:47:25.834485','Why is acclimatization important at high altitudes?','The text mentions that high altitude affects breathing, so climbers must adjust slowly.'),(72,'2025-06-02 14:47:56.536131',_binary '','2025-06-02 14:47:56.536138','What do crampons help with?','Crampons are metal spikes that provide grip on ice.'),(73,'2025-06-02 15:13:45.104893',_binary '','2025-06-02 15:13:45.104904','What is a \"timetable\" used for?','The text defines a timetable as a schedule of train times.'),(74,'2025-06-02 15:14:13.265244',_binary '','2025-06-02 15:14:13.265254','What is the advantage of a reservation?','The text states that reservations ensure a confirmed seat.'),(75,'2025-06-02 15:14:38.128105',_binary '','2025-06-02 15:14:38.128131','Who checks your ticket on the train?','The conductor is responsible for checking tickets.'),(76,'2025-06-02 15:19:05.095008',_binary '','2025-06-02 15:19:05.095026','Why do some people prefer studying in coffee shops?','The text mentions that ambient noise can improve concentration.'),(77,'2025-06-02 15:19:40.981962',_binary '','2025-06-02 15:19:40.981983','What should you look for when choosing a study spot in a café?','The text lists Wi-Fi and power outlets as important features.'),(78,'2025-06-02 15:20:43.581982',_binary '','2025-06-02 15:20:43.581993','What is a \"barista\"?','The text defines a barista as someone who prepares coffee.'),(79,'2025-06-11 14:30:35.486897',_binary '','2025-06-11 14:30:35.486897','What is the meaning of \"lush\" when describing a park?','\"Lush\" is an adjective that describes vegetation that is healthy, green, and growing abundantly. It refers to the rich, vibrant plant life in a park.'),(80,'2025-06-11 14:31:10.075316',_binary '','2025-06-11 14:31:10.075316','Which activity involves eating outdoors in a park setting?','A picnic specifically refers to eating a meal outdoors, typically in a park or natural setting. The other options describe different recreational activities but don\'t involve eating.'),(81,'2025-06-11 14:31:46.275786',_binary '','2025-06-11 14:31:46.275786','If someone walks \"leisurely\" through a park, how are they moving?','\"Leisurely\" is an adverb that means doing something in a relaxed way without hurrying. It describes a calm, unhurried pace of movement.'),(82,'2025-06-11 14:32:13.511756',_binary '','2025-06-11 14:32:13.511756','What is the primary purpose of a playground in a park?','A playground is specifically designed as an area with equipment like swings, slides, and climbing structures where children can play safely and have fun.'),(83,'2025-06-11 14:32:38.867611',_binary '','2025-06-11 14:32:38.867611','Which word best describes the opposite of a \"spacious\" park?','\"Spacious\" means having plenty of room or space. The opposite would be \"crowded,\" meaning filled with too many people or things, leaving little free space. The other options describe different qualities that don\'t relate to space.'),(84,'2025-06-11 14:39:26.207835',_binary '','2025-06-11 14:39:26.207835','What is the main difference between a \"quiz\" and an \"examination\"?','A quiz is generally a short test covering recent material, while an examination is more comprehensive and covers broader content, often given at major points in the course.'),(85,'2025-06-11 14:39:54.975495',_binary '','2025-06-11 14:39:54.975495','If a student approaches a test \"carefully,\" how are they taking it?','\"Carefully\" means doing something with attention, precision, and thought. Taking a test carefully means reading questions thoroughly and thinking before answering.'),(86,'2025-06-11 14:40:22.669596',_binary '','2025-06-11 14:40:22.669596','What does it mean to \"review\" before a test?','\"Review\" means to examine or study something again, typically material that has been previously learned, to refresh one\'s memory before a test.'),(87,'2025-06-11 14:48:23.374016',_binary '','2025-06-11 14:49:34.252820','What is the primary function of a \"controller\" in gaming?','A controller is the input device that allows players to send commands to the game, such as moving characters, jumping, or performing actions through buttons and joysticks.'),(88,'2025-06-11 14:49:28.129114',_binary '','2025-06-11 14:49:28.129114',' If a game is described as \"addictive,\" what does this mean?',' \"Addictive\" in gaming context means the game is so enjoyable and compelling that players find it hard to stop playing and want to continue for extended periods.'),(89,'2025-06-11 14:57:34.000291',_binary '','2025-06-11 14:57:34.000291','What is the \"summit\" of a mountain?','The \"summit\" refers to the topmost point of a mountain - the ultimate goal that climbers aim to reach. It\'s the highest elevation point of the mountain.'),(90,'2025-06-11 14:58:00.286831',_binary '','2025-06-11 14:58:00.286831','When climbers \"descend\" a mountain, what are they doing?','\"Descend\" means to go down or move from a higher place to a lower place. After reaching the summit, climbers must descend back down the mountain.'),(91,'2025-06-11 14:58:30.654295',_binary '','2025-06-11 14:58:30.654295','What does it mean when a mountain path is described as \"steep\"?','\"Steep\" describes something that rises or falls at a sharp angle, making it difficult to climb. A steep mountain path has a sharp upward incline.'),(92,'2025-06-11 14:58:55.136856',_binary '','2025-06-11 14:58:55.136856','Why do mountain climbers need to move \"carefully\"?','Moving \"carefully\" means being cautious and paying attention to safety. Mountain climbing involves risks like falling rocks, unstable surfaces, and steep drops, so careful movement is essential.'),(93,'2025-06-11 14:59:31.080000',_binary '','2025-06-11 14:59:31.080000','If someone describes a mountain view as \"breathtaking,\" they mean it is:','\"Breathtaking\" is used figuratively to describe something so beautiful, impressive, or amazing that it metaphorically takes your breath away. It describes spectacular mountain views that are awe-inspiring.'),(94,'2025-06-11 15:08:49.643702',_binary '','2025-06-11 15:08:49.643702','What is the main difference between a regular train and an \"express\" train?','An \"express\" train is designed for speed and efficiency, making limited stops only at major stations, allowing it to reach destinations faster than regular trains that stop at every station.'),(95,'2025-06-11 15:10:40.151294',_binary '','2025-06-11 15:10:40.151294','What is the main difference between a regular train and an \"express\" train?','An \"express\" train is designed for speed and efficiency, making limited stops only at major stations, allowing it to reach destinations faster than regular trains that stop at every station.'),(96,'2025-06-11 15:14:50.989586',_binary '','2025-06-11 15:14:50.989586','What role does the \"atmosphere\" play in a study cafe?','\"Atmosphere\" refers to the overall feeling, mood, and environment of a place. In a study cafe, the atmosphere includes factors like lighting, music, decor, and general ambiance that can influence how well students can focus and study.'),(97,'2025-06-11 15:15:16.420880',_binary '','2025-06-11 15:15:16.420880','When students \"brainstorm\" at a cafe, what are they doing?','\"Brainstorm\" means to generate ideas creatively, often in a group setting. Students brainstorming at a cafe are working together to come up with solutions, concepts, or approaches for their projects or assignments.'),(98,'2025-06-11 15:15:43.050851',_binary '','2025-06-11 15:15:43.050851','If a study session at a cafe is described as \"productive,\" it means:','\"Productive\" means achieving a significant amount of useful work or results. A productive study session means the student accomplished their learning goals and made good progress on their academic tasks.'),(99,'2025-06-11 15:16:07.987810',_binary '','2025-06-11 15:16:07.987810','What does \"ambient\" noise refer to in a cafe setting?','\"Ambient\" refers to the surrounding environment. Ambient noise includes all the background sounds in a cafe - gentle conversations, soft music, coffee machines, and general activity that creates the overall sound environment.'),(100,'2025-06-11 15:23:40.697567',_binary '','2025-06-11 15:23:40.697567','What is an \"algorithm\" in the context of AI development?','An algorithm is a step-by-step procedure or set of rules designed to solve a specific problem or perform a task. In AI, algorithms are the mathematical instructions that enable machines to learn, make decisions, and process information.'),(101,'2025-06-11 15:24:06.340492',_binary '','2025-06-11 15:24:06.340492','What does it mean when AI development is described as \"revolutionary\"?','\"Revolutionary\" means causing or involving a complete or dramatic change. Revolutionary AI development refers to breakthroughs that fundamentally transform industries, society, or how we interact with technology.'),(102,'2025-06-11 15:24:35.870166',_binary '','2025-06-11 15:24:35.870166','When AI systems \"process\" data, what are they doing?','\"Process\" in AI context means to analyze, transform, and work with data to extract meaningful information, patterns, or results. AI systems process data to learn, make predictions, or generate outputs.'),(103,'2025-06-11 15:25:04.891899',_binary '','2025-06-11 15:25:04.892480','What is the primary purpose of a \"dataset\" in AI development?','A dataset is a collection of data used to train AI models. It provides the examples and information that AI systems need to learn patterns, make associations, and develop the ability to perform specific tasks.'),(104,'2025-06-11 15:25:38.230132',_binary '','2025-06-11 15:25:38.230682','If AI technology is developing \"rapidly,\" this means:',' \"Rapidly\" means quickly or at a fast rate. Rapid AI development indicates that new advances, improvements, and breakthroughs are occurring frequently and at an accelerated pace in the field of artificial intelligence.'),(105,'2025-06-11 15:29:05.838209',_binary '','2025-06-11 15:29:05.838209','What is the main purpose of a \"workout\" in maintaining health?','A \"workout\" is a session of physical exercise designed to improve health, strength, endurance, or overall fitness. The primary goal is to enhance physical condition through structured physical activity.'),(106,'2025-06-11 15:41:12.924054',_binary '','2025-06-11 15:41:12.924054','What is the primary role of a \"librarian\" in a library?','A librarian is a trained professional who helps library users locate books and information, provides guidance on library services, organizes collections, and ensures the library operates smoothly for all patrons.'),(107,'2025-06-11 15:52:49.371099',_binary '','2025-06-11 15:52:49.371099','Choose the correct sentence using past perfect tense:','Past perfect uses \"had + past participle.\" The past participle of \"go\" is \"gone,\" not \"went.\" Option B correctly shows that going to the store happened before the store closed.'),(108,'2025-06-11 15:53:15.543624',_binary '','2025-06-11 15:53:15.543624','Which sentence correctly shows the time sequence of past events?','The past perfect \"had eaten\" shows the first action (eating dinner), and simple past \"watched\" shows the second action (watching TV). This correctly sequences the events.'),(109,'2025-06-11 15:53:40.194978',_binary '','2025-06-11 15:53:40.194978','Select the correct negative form of past perfect:','The negative form of past perfect is \"had not\" (hadn\'t) + past participle. Option C is correct, while A has a double negative, B mixes tenses incorrectly, and D uses present perfect.'),(110,'2025-06-11 15:54:03.260790',_binary '','2025-06-11 15:54:03.260790','When do we use past perfect tense?','Past perfect is specifically used to indicate that one past action was completed before another past action or time. It establishes the sequence of past events.'),(111,'2025-06-11 15:54:31.838005',_binary '','2025-06-11 15:54:31.838005','Choose the correct question form using past perfect:','Past perfect questions are formed by putting \"had\" before the subject, followed by the past participle. Option C correctly shows this structure and indicates that finishing work happened before the phone call.'),(112,'2025-06-11 15:59:57.969772',_binary '','2025-06-11 15:59:57.969772','Choose the correct future perfect sentence:','Future perfect uses \"will have + past participle.\" Option B correctly shows an action that will be completed before a specific future time (next year).'),(113,'2025-06-11 16:00:55.969197',_binary '','2025-06-11 16:00:55.969197','Which sentence shows the correct use of future perfect?','Future perfect shows completion before a future time. \"Will have finished\" correctly indicates the project will be completed before Friday arrives.'),(114,'2025-06-11 16:07:47.652008',_binary '','2025-06-11 16:07:47.652008','Choose the correct future continuous sentence:','Future continuous uses \"will be + verb-ing\" to show an action in progress at a specific future time.'),(115,'2025-06-11 16:08:11.754430',_binary '','2025-06-11 16:08:11.754430','Which sentence shows the correct use of future continuous?','Future continuous requires \"will be + present participle (-ing form).\" \"Traveling\" is the correct -ing form of \"travel.\"'),(116,'2025-06-11 16:08:37.671627',_binary '','2025-06-11 16:08:37.671627','Select the correct negative form of future continuous:','The negative form places \"not\" after \"will\" and before \"be\": \"will not be + verb-ing.\" Option A follows this correct structure.'),(117,'2025-06-11 16:09:04.528344',_binary '','2025-06-11 16:09:04.528344','When do we use future continuous tense?','Future continuous specifically describes actions that will be ongoing or in progress at a particular moment in the future, not completed actions.'),(118,'2025-06-11 16:13:26.157525',_binary '','2025-06-11 16:13:26.157525','Choose the correct past continuous sentence:','Past continuous uses \"was/were + verb-ing\" to show an action in progress at a specific past time. Option B correctly indicates watching was ongoing at 9 PM yesterday.'),(119,'2025-06-11 16:17:44.698401',_binary '','2025-06-11 16:17:44.698401','Choose the correct First Conditional sentence:','First Conditional uses \"If + present simple, will + base verb\" to express real future possibilities. We never use \"will\" in the if clause itself.'),(120,'2025-06-11 16:19:57.119089',_binary '','2025-06-11 16:19:57.119089','Choose the correct passive voice sentence:','Passive voice uses \"be + past participle.\" The past participle of \"write\" is \"written,\" not \"wrote.\" \"Was written\" correctly shows past passive voice.'),(121,'2025-06-11 16:24:03.198898',_binary '','2025-06-11 16:24:03.198898','Which sentence correctly uses a non-defining relative clause?','Non-defining relative clauses provide extra information and are set off by commas. If you have only one brother, the information is additional, not essential to identify which brother.'),(122,'2025-06-11 16:33:41.020834',_binary '','2025-06-11 16:33:41.020834','Why was Sarah\'s mom always tired and stressed?','The text clearly states that \"my mom was always tired and stressed because she was doing all the household chores by herself\" including preparing breakfast, cleaning, laundry, vacuuming, and organizing rooms.'),(123,'2025-06-11 16:34:07.138208',_binary '','2025-06-11 16:34:07.138208','What motivated Sarah to talk to her family about helping more?','Sarah was motivated when she \"noticed my mom sitting on the couch looking very tired after a long day of cleaning\" and felt sad, which prompted her to take action.'),(124,'2025-06-11 16:43:57.278219',_binary '','2025-06-11 16:43:57.278219','What was the main challenge Lisa and David faced when planning their wedding?','The text states that \"Lisa dreamed of an outdoor garden ceremony\" while \"David preferred a traditional church wedding,\" showing they had different location preferences that required compromise.'),(125,'2025-06-11 16:52:18.798038',_binary '','2025-06-11 16:52:18.798038','How long did Jake and Maria save money for their European trip?','The text clearly states \"We had been saving money for eight months and finally had enough for our dream vacation.\"'),(126,'2025-06-11 16:58:54.737289',_binary '','2025-06-11 16:58:54.737289','How did Emma initially react when the first firework exploded?','The text describes \"a thunderous boom that made Emma jump and grab my hand\" followed by \"Emma\'s initial fear quickly turned to excitement as more fireworks followed.\"'),(127,'2025-06-11 16:59:18.060145',_binary '','2025-06-11 16:59:18.060145','What did the narrator observe about the crowd during the fireworks display?','The narrator describes watching different age groups enjoying the show and notes \"all the everyday worries and differences that might divide us seemed to disappear. We were simply a community united in wonder.\"'),(128,'2025-06-11 17:04:00.109724',_binary '','2025-06-11 17:04:00.109724','What advice did Ms. Rodriguez give about making mistakes in music?','Ms. Rodriguez said \"Music is not about being flawless, it\'s about expressing your soul through sound\" and taught that \"making mistakes was part of learning, and that persistence was more important than perfection.\"'),(129,'2025-06-11 17:07:55.108827',_binary '','2025-06-11 17:07:55.108827','How did Emily and Alex first become partners?','The text states \"our teacher, Mr. Peterson, assigned lab partners for the entire semester\" and \"Emily Rodriguez and Alex Chen,\" Mr. Peterson announced, showing they were assigned by the teacher.'),(130,'2025-06-11 17:08:23.326641',_binary '','2025-06-11 17:08:23.326641','What was Alex\'s first romantic gesture toward Emily?','The text describes how \"Alex handed me a small origami crane he had made during lunch\" and explained it was for good luck, which was his first romantic gesture.'),(131,'2025-06-11 18:58:36.040430',_binary '','2025-06-11 18:58:36.040430','How much total money does the organizing committee have available for the festival?','How much total money does the organizing committee have available for the festival?'),(132,'2025-06-11 19:24:00.435920',_binary '','2025-06-11 19:24:00.435920','How often does James typically bring clients to The Golden Fork?','James clearly states \"I bring important clients here at least twice a month for dinner meetings\" when explaining his patronage of the restaurant.'),(133,'2025-06-13 16:11:03.362834',_binary '','2025-06-13 16:11:03.362834','What do you call the list of food and drinks available at a restaurant?','A menu is the list that shows all available food and drinks with their prices at a restaurant.'),(134,'2025-06-13 16:23:31.585622',_binary '','2025-06-13 16:23:31.585622','What is the correct way to describe tomorrow\'s weather forecast?','When making predictions about future weather, we use \"will\" + base verb or \"going to\" + base verb. \"It will be sunny tomorrow\" is the correct future tense structure for weather predictions.'),(135,'2025-06-13 16:29:03.743251',_binary '','2025-06-13 16:29:03.743251','Which sentence correctly introduces a family member using possessive adjectives?','\"This is my older sister, Sarah\" correctly uses \"my\" to show the relationship and introduces the person by name'),(136,'2025-06-13 16:34:40.058050',_binary '','2025-06-13 16:34:40.058050','What is the correct way to ask for help when shopping for clothes?','\"Could you help me find a dress in size medium?\" is the most polite and appropriate way to request help from a shop assistant.'),(137,'2025-06-13 16:39:41.311322',_binary '','2025-06-13 16:39:41.311322','Which sentence correctly uses \"there is\" and \"there are\" to describe what\'s in a house?','\"There are three bedrooms and there is one bathroom upstairs\" correctly uses \"there are\" for the plural \"bedrooms\" and \"there is\" for the singular \"bathroom.\"'),(138,'2025-06-13 16:42:46.469473',_binary '','2025-06-13 16:42:46.469473','What is the correct way to politely ask for directions?','When asking for directions politely, we use \"Could you\" or \"Can you\" + \"tell me\" + question word. \"Could you tell me how to get to the train station?\" is the most polite and appropriate way to ask for directions from strangers.'),(139,'2025-06-13 16:45:30.397935',_binary '','2025-06-13 16:45:30.397935','What is the correct way to request a medical appointment over the phone?','When making formal requests like medical appointments, we use polite structures with \"I would like to\" or \"Could I.\" \"I would like to schedule an appointment with Dr. Smith\" is the most professional and appropriate way to request an appointment.'),(140,'2025-06-13 16:50:09.177133',_binary '','2025-06-13 16:50:09.177133','What is the correct way to talk about regular weekend activities?','When describing habitual or regular activities, we use the present simple tense with frequency adverbs. \"I usually go hiking on weekends\" correctly shows a regular weekend activity using \"usually\" and present simple tense.'),(141,'2025-06-13 16:53:12.353679',_binary '','2025-06-13 16:53:12.353679','What is the correct way to ask about the location of items in a supermarket?','\"Where can I find the dairy products?\" is the most polite and natural way to ask for help locating items.'),(142,'2025-06-13 16:56:34.030203',_binary '','2025-06-13 16:56:34.030745','What is the correct way to describe someone\'s physical appearance?',' \"She has long brown hair and blue eyes\" correctly uses \"has\" to describe physical characteristics.'),(143,'2025-06-13 17:00:05.980683',_binary '','2025-06-13 17:00:05.980683','What is the correct way to ask about bus routes and destinations?',' \"Which bus goes to the city center?\" is the proper way to inquire about routes to specific destinations.'),(144,'2025-06-13 17:02:29.849460',_binary '','2025-06-13 17:02:29.849460','What is the correct way to ask someone for their phone number?','\"Could you give me your phone number?\" is the most polite and appropriate way to ask for someone\'s contact details.'),(145,'2025-06-13 20:02:04.415005',_binary '','2025-06-13 20:02:04.415005','Which sentence represents a correct First Conditional structure?','First Conditional uses present tense in the if-clause (\"have\") and future tense (\"will call\") in the main clause. This structure expresses a real possibility in the future.'),(146,'2025-06-13 20:09:54.414069',_binary '','2025-06-13 20:09:54.414069','Transform this active sentence to passive: \"The chef prepared the meal.\"','To convert active to passive, the object \"the meal\" becomes the subject, we use the appropriate form of \"be\" (was/were) with the past participle \"prepared,\" and the original subject becomes optional \"by the chef.\"'),(147,'2025-06-13 20:24:27.614250',_binary '','2025-06-13 20:24:27.614250','Transform to reported speech: \"I will call you tomorrow,\" he said.','When reporting this statement, \"will\" changes to \"would,\" \"I\" changes to \"he,\" \"you\" changes to the appropriate pronoun based on context, and \"tomorrow\" changes to \"the next day\" or \"the following day.\"'),(148,'2025-06-14 15:42:32.029919',_binary '','2025-06-14 15:42:32.029919','She is ___ honest person who always tells ___ truth.','\"Honest\" starts with a vowel sound /ɒ/, so we use \"an.\" \"Truth\" is a specific concept that both speaker and listener understand, and it\'s also an abstract noun that typically takes \"the\" when referring to the concept of truth in general.'),(149,'2025-06-14 15:45:23.646776',_binary '','2025-06-14 15:45:23.646776','She suggested ___ to the new restaurant downtown.','The verb \"suggest\" is always followed by a gerund, not an infinitive. After \"suggest,\" we use verb + -ing form. \"Suggest to go\" is incorrect in English.'),(150,'2025-06-14 15:48:51.620172',_binary '','2025-06-14 15:48:51.620172','Choose the correct relative pronoun: \"The woman ___ lives next door is a doctor.\"',' \"Who\" is used for people when they are the subject of the relative clause. \"Which\" is for things, \"whose\" shows possession, and \"whom\" is for objects.'),(151,'2025-06-14 15:51:17.990208',_binary '','2025-06-14 15:51:17.990208','Choose the correct comparative form: \"Learning English is ___ than I expected.\"','We don\'t use \"the\" with comparative forms unless there\'s a specific context requiring it.'),(152,'2025-06-14 15:53:41.394336',_binary '','2025-06-14 15:53:41.394336','Choose the correct modal: \"You ___ wear a helmet when riding a motorcycle. It\'s the law.\"','\"Must\" expresses strong necessity or obligation, especially when it\'s a rule, law, or requirement. \"Should\" is for advice, \"can\" is for ability, and \"might\" is for possibility.'),(153,'2025-06-14 15:57:18.938334',_binary '','2025-06-14 15:57:18.938334','Choose the correct subjunctive form: \"The teacher insists that every student ___ the assignment on time.\"','After verbs like \"insist,\" \"suggest,\" \"demand,\" and \"require,\" we use the subjunctive mood with the base form of the verb (without -s) regardless of the subject.'),(154,'2025-06-14 16:00:17.558807',_binary '','2025-06-14 16:00:17.558807','Choose the sentence with correct parallel structure:','Parallel structure requires the same grammatical form for items in a series. Option B correctly uses three gerunds (swimming, running, cycling).'),(155,'2025-06-14 16:02:36.002735',_binary '','2025-06-14 16:02:36.002735','Choose the correct verb: \"The collection of rare books ___ very valuable.\"\n','The true subject is \"collection\" (singular), not \"books.\" The prepositional phrase \"of rare books\" modifies the subject but doesn\'t affect verb agreement.'),(156,'2025-06-14 16:11:50.028672',_binary '','2025-06-14 16:11:50.029219','What is the recommended room temperature for a newborn\'s sleep environment?\n','The text specifically states that keeping the room at a comfortable temperature of \"around 68-70°F (20-21°C) is ideal\" for newborn sleep.'),(157,'2025-06-14 16:17:42.414501',_binary '','2025-06-14 16:17:42.414501','According to Ms. Johnson, what is the maximum recommended duration for a time-out for a three-year-old?','Ms. Johnson specifically states that \"Time-outs can be effective for three-year-olds, but they should be brief – about three minutes maximum.\"'),(158,'2025-06-14 16:21:08.994638',_binary '','2025-06-14 16:21:08.994638','What time did Sarah set her alarm to prepare for her presentation?','Sarah clearly states in her email \"I set my alarm for 6:30 AM to give myself plenty of time for my 8:30 presentation.\"'),(159,'2025-06-14 16:25:38.293906',_binary '','2025-06-14 16:25:38.293906','How long did Emma spend planning her grocery shopping trip?','Emma states \"I have everything organized by store sections with approximate prices. I\'ve been planning this for three days.\"'),(160,'2025-06-14 16:29:22.781889',_binary '','2025-06-14 16:29:22.781889','What TV show does Lisa want to watch?','Lisa clearly states \"Because I want to watch the season finale of \'The Crown\'\" when asking about the remote control.'),(161,'2025-06-14 16:34:21.315394',_binary '','2025-06-14 16:34:21.315394','What is the weight accuracy requirement Marcus initially set for the food dispensing?','Marcus writes \"we need to dispense exactly 50 grams of food per serving with less than 2% error rate\" in his first journal entry.'),(162,'2025-06-14 16:40:17.591550',_binary '','2025-06-14 16:40:17.591550','How much money has TechLover2024 spent on gadgets in six months?','SimpleLifeSarah states \"In six months, he\'s spent over $800 on devices that do things we could do perfectly fine with our hands.\"'),(163,'2025-06-14 18:18:38.526315',_binary '','2025-06-14 18:18:38.526315','What was the original custom WiFi password that Alex and Jamie had been using?','Alex mentions \"I\'m using the same password we\'ve had for months: \'Netflix2024!\'\" when describing the connection problem.'),(164,'2025-06-14 18:23:59.581535',_binary '','2025-06-14 18:23:59.581535','What is Alex\'s typical approach to seasoning food?','Maya describes Alex\'s preferences: \"Alex loves everything spicy – the hotter, the better. His idea of seasoning is to add jalapeños to everything, including his morning eggs.\"'),(165,'2025-06-14 18:29:25.889023',_binary '','2025-06-14 18:29:25.889023','What gaming element does Lily compare to football teamwork?','Lily explains \"It\'s like a multiplayer raid in an online game where everyone has specific responsibilities and must coordinate perfectly.\"'),(166,'2025-06-14 18:34:06.194283',_binary '','2025-06-14 18:34:06.194283','How much money did David and Sarah save in December through his cost-cutting strategies?','David states \"I\'m happy to report we saved $847 last month by following my cost-cutting strategies.\"'),(167,'2025-06-15 14:52:23.854559',_binary '','2025-06-15 14:52:23.854559','What was Mike\'s main problem with understanding the recipe?','Mike specifically mentions that he couldn\'t figure out what \"a pinch of cinnamon\" meant and ended up using half a jar instead of the tiny amount intended.'),(168,'2025-06-15 15:06:01.484599',_binary '','2025-06-15 15:06:01.485165','What does Yuki believe is most important in Japanese cooking?','Yuki specifically states that \"in Japanese cooking, we believe in simplicity\" and that \"the natural flavor of each ingredient should shine through,\" contrasting with Jake\'s twelve-ingredient approach.'),(169,'2025-06-15 15:14:04.143766',_binary '','2025-06-15 15:14:04.143766','Why did Emma\'s cookies look like \"abstract art\"?','Emma explains that she didn\'t have a heart-shaped cookie cutter, so she tried to cut the cookies by hand with a knife, which made them look like abstract art rather than proper heart shapes.'),(170,'2025-06-15 15:18:41.694228',_binary '','2025-06-15 15:18:41.694228','What is Tom\'s main challenge with yoga?','Tom mentions that \"the most flexible thing about me is my work schedule\" and later says he \"spends most of his time at a desk job,\" indicating his lack of flexibility is due to his sedentary work lifestyle.'),(171,'2025-06-15 15:47:49.070289',_binary '','2025-06-15 15:47:49.070289','How did Alex and Jordan feel after their very first training run?','Jordan mentions they \"couldn\'t even make it around the block without stopping\" and thought they\'d \"made a terrible mistake,\" while Alex describes them \"wheezing like old steam engines\" after just half a mile.'),(172,'2025-06-15 16:02:02.412344',_binary '','2025-06-15 16:02:02.412344','What was Marcus\'s original plan for the fishing trip?','Marcus mentions it \"was supposed to be my chance to show Rachel the ropes\" and \"teach her the fine art of fishing,\" indicating he wanted to be the instructor and demonstrate his expertise.'),(173,'2025-06-15 16:25:11.746846',_binary '','2025-06-15 16:25:11.746846','What type of painting were Sophie and Kevin supposed to create?','Sophie mentions they \"signed up for \'Peaceful Sunset Over Mountains\'\" at the beginning of the conversation, indicating this was the intended subject of their painting.'),(174,'2025-06-15 16:43:39.584523',_binary '','2025-06-15 16:43:39.584523','What type of painting were Sophie and Kevin supposed to create?','Sophie mentions they \"signed up for \'Peaceful Sunset Over Mountains\'\" at the beginning of the conversation, indicating this was the intended subject of their painting.'),(175,'2025-06-15 16:46:42.460677',_binary '','2025-06-15 16:46:42.460677','How did the audience react to Sarah\'s performance of \"I Will Always Love You\"?','Amy describes that \"the entire room went silent during her performance. You could hear a pin drop\" and Jake later mentions that \"Sarah got that standing ovation,\" indicating respectful silence during the song followed by enthusiastic applause.'),(176,'2025-06-15 16:58:27.724066',_binary '','2025-06-15 16:58:27.724066','Why did Chris and Taylor\'s DIY project end up being more expensive than expected?','Taylor mentions \"between the three trips to the hardware store, the replacement wood, and all those extra screws we somehow needed, we could have bought a professional bookshelf,\" indicating multiple shopping trips and replacement materials drove up costs.'),(177,'2025-06-15 17:11:36.183674',_binary '','2025-06-15 17:11:36.183674','Why did Ryan suggest ignoring Google Maps during their trip?','Ryan explains that he \"thought it would be more adventurous to explore some back roads\" and mentions his \"sense of direction has always been pretty reliable,\" indicating he preferred adventure and trusted his instincts over technology.');
