INSERT INTO `question` (`id`, `created_at`, `status`, `updated_at`, `content`, `explanation`) VALUES (1,'2025-05-17 10:34:35.087371',_binary '','2025-05-17 10:34:35.087381','According to the passage, the current rate of species extinction is:','The passage explicitly states in the first paragraph that \"the current rate of species loss is between 100 and 1,000 times higher than natural extinction rates.\"'),(2,'2025-05-17 10:35:15.092425',_binary '','2025-05-17 10:35:15.092437','Which of the following is NOT mentioned as a function of protected areas?','The passage mentions biodiversity preservation, ecosystem services (including carbon sequestration, which is related to but different from reducing industrial emissions), and economic benefits through ecotourism.'),(3,'2025-05-17 10:36:37.671603',_binary '','2025-05-17 10:36:37.671612','According to the passage, the term \"robot\" originated from:','The passage states in the first paragraph that the term \"robot\" was coined by Czech playwright Karel Čapek and is \"derived from the Czech word \'robota,\' meaning forced labor or servitude.\"'),(4,'2025-05-17 10:37:38.768214',_binary '','2025-05-17 10:37:38.768233','What was significant about George Devol\'s Unimate?','According to the second paragraph, \"In 1954, George Devol created the first programmable robotic arm, the Unimate, which was installed at a General Motors plant in 1961, marking the beginning of industrial robotics.\"'),(5,'2025-05-17 10:39:14.755540',_binary '','2025-05-31 17:55:13.757431','What are the advantages of studying online compared to traditional classrooms?','Consider flexibility, cost, and accessibility. Mention how online learning allows students to learn from anywhere and access a variety of resources.'),(6,'2025-05-17 10:39:14.765610',_binary '','2025-05-31 17:55:27.700540','What challenges do students face in online education?','Discuss issues like lack of motivation, distractions at home, and limited social interaction.'),(7,'2025-05-17 10:44:47.703300',_binary '','2025-05-17 10:44:47.703312','What causes ocean acidification according to the marine biologist?','The marine biologist states that \"As the ocean absorbs carbon dioxide from the atmosphere, it forms carbonic acid, gradually lowering the ocean\'s pH.\"'),(8,'2025-05-17 10:45:46.132878',_binary '','2025-05-17 10:45:46.132886','By what percentage have ocean surface waters become more acidic since the Industrial Revolution?','According to the transcript, \"Since the Industrial Revolution, ocean surface waters have become about 30% more acidic.\"'),(9,'2025-05-17 11:10:12.631117',_binary '','2025-05-17 11:10:12.631136','What is meaning of environment?','Meaning of \"environment\" is môi trường'),(10,'2025-05-17 11:11:21.445115',_binary '','2025-05-17 11:11:21.445121','What\'s sentence right ?','This is explaination'),(11,'2025-05-17 11:12:38.723792',_binary '','2025-05-17 11:12:38.723799','According to the passage, the current rate of species extinction is:','The passage explicitly states in the first paragraph that \"the current rate of species loss is between 100 and 1,000 times higher than natural extinction rates.\"'),(12,'2025-05-17 11:13:51.017520',_binary '','2025-05-17 11:13:51.017524','What causes ocean acidification according to the marine biologist?','The marine biologist states that \"As the ocean absorbs carbon dioxide from the atmosphere, it forms carbonic acid, gradually lowering the ocean\'s pH.\"'),(13,'2025-05-17 11:14:29.646319',_binary '','2025-05-31 16:15:16.651362','What do you like most about your hometown?','This question checks your ability to describe a familiar place with personal opinions and reasons'),(14,'2025-05-19 14:01:06.109883',_binary '','2025-05-19 14:01:06.109894','Q1','E1'),(15,'2025-05-19 14:01:24.571895',_binary '','2025-05-19 14:01:24.571907','Q1','E1'),(18,'2025-05-19 14:03:05.374876',_binary '','2025-05-31 17:09:21.637872','What do you do to stay healthy?','This question assesses your ability to describe routines and habits using present simple and relevant vocabulary (e.g., exercise, diet).'),(19,'2025-05-31 15:43:00.434255',_binary '','2025-05-31 15:43:00.434270','Can you describe your typical day from morning to evening?','Talk about your daily routine. Use time phrases like \"In the morning,\" \"After school,\" \"At night.\" Add personal examples.'),(20,'2025-05-31 15:43:00.471809',_binary '','2025-05-31 15:43:00.471813','What is one habit you would like to change or improve? Why?','Mention a habit like procrastination or sleeping late. Explain how changing it could improve your life (e.g., more energy, better focus).'),(21,'2025-05-31 15:43:33.560002',_binary '','2025-05-31 15:43:33.560007','How do you use technology in your daily life?','Mention tools like phones, computers, apps. Include how they help with work, study, or entertainment.'),(22,'2025-05-31 15:43:33.576290',_binary '','2025-05-31 15:43:33.576299','Do you think people rely too much on technology nowadays?','Share your opinion with reasons. You could say \"Yes, because...\" or \"No, because...\" Support with examples like social media use or online shopping.'),(23,'2025-05-31 08:50:45.000000',_binary '','2025-05-31 08:50:45.000000','The company is planning to _____ a new product next month.','“Launch a product” is the correct business collocation. Other options don’t fit the context.'),(24,'2025-05-31 08:50:45.000000',_binary '','2025-05-31 08:50:45.000000','She gave an impressive _____ on climate change.','A “presentation” is a formal speech. Other words are inappropriate.'),(25,'2025-05-31 08:50:45.000000',_binary '','2025-05-31 08:50:45.000000','We need to _____ the risk before making a decision.','“Evaluate” means to assess or analyze risks before deciding.'),(26,'2025-05-31 08:50:45.000000',_binary '','2025-05-31 08:50:45.000000','The museum is famous for its rare _____ of ancient coins.','“Collection” fits a group of items like coins.'),(27,'2025-05-31 08:50:45.000000',_binary '','2025-05-31 08:50:45.000000','He has a very _____ schedule this week, so he can’t meet us.','“Heavy schedule” is the correct collocation.'),(28,'2025-05-31 08:50:45.000000',_binary '','2025-05-31 08:50:45.000000','They finally _____ an agreement after long discussions.','“Reach an agreement” is the standard collocation.'),(29,'2025-05-31 08:50:45.000000',_binary '','2025-05-31 08:50:45.000000','The book provides a _____ description of life in the 1800s.','“Vivid” means clear and detailed. The opposite of “dull.”'),(30,'2025-05-31 08:50:45.000000',_binary '','2025-05-31 08:50:45.000000','Students must _____ to the rules of the school.','“Adhere to” means to follow or obey rules strictly.'),(31,'2025-05-31 08:50:45.000000',_binary '','2025-05-31 08:50:45.000000','She showed great _____ in solving the problem.','“Creativity” is the ability to think of new ideas or solve problems.'),(32,'2025-05-31 08:50:45.000000',_binary '','2025-05-31 08:50:45.000000','The manager gave a very _____ explanation of the issue.','“Clear” is the correct adjective to describe an explanation.'),(33,'2025-05-31 08:50:45.000000',_binary '','2025-05-31 08:50:45.000000','If I _____ more money, I would travel the world.','This is a second conditional sentence: if + past simple → would + base verb.'),(34,'2025-05-31 08:50:45.000000',_binary '','2025-05-31 08:50:45.000000','She _____ to the gym every morning.','Present simple tense: \"She\" requires \"goes.\"'),(35,'2025-05-31 08:50:45.000000',_binary '','2025-05-31 08:50:45.000000','I have lived here _____ five years.','“For” + duration, “since” is used with a point in time.'),(36,'2025-05-31 08:50:45.000000',_binary '','2025-05-31 08:50:45.000000','He is the man _____ helped me yesterday.','“Who” is used as the subject for people.'),(37,'2025-05-31 08:50:45.000000',_binary '','2025-05-31 08:50:45.000000','They _____ dinner when I arrived.','Past continuous tense describes an action in progress.'),(38,'2025-05-31 0