y _____ answer to the interviewer.','“Honest” means truthful and sincere.'),(50,'2025-05-31 08:58:43.000000',_binary '','2025-05-31 08:58:43.000000','The staff needs proper _____ to handle emergencies.','“Training” is essential for preparedness.'),(51,'2025-05-31 08:58:43.000000',_binary '','2025-05-31 08:58:43.000000','The team needs a clear _____ to move forward.','“Strategy” is a plan of action.'),(52,'2025-05-31 08:58:43.000000',_binary '','2025-05-31 08:58:43.000000','He spoke in a very _____ tone, which made others feel calm.','“Gentle” means soft or kind.'),(53,'2025-05-31 08:58:43.000000',_binary '','2025-05-31 08:58:43.000000','By the time we arrived, the film _____ already started.','Past perfect tense: “had started.”'),(54,'2025-05-31 08:58:43.000000',_binary '','2025-05-31 08:58:43.000000','I wish I _____ more time to relax.','Unreal wish in present: “had.”'),(55,'2025-05-31 08:58:43.000000',_binary '','2025-05-31 08:58:43.000000','She _____ studying when I called her.','Past continuous tense.'),(56,'2025-05-31 08:58:43.000000',_binary '','2025-05-31 08:58:43.000000','This is the restaurant _____ we had dinner yesterday.','“Where” is used for place.'),(57,'2025-05-31 08:58:43.000000',_binary '','2025-05-31 08:58:43.000000','Neither my brother nor my friends _____ coming today.','Use verb agreement with the subject closer to the verb.'),(58,'2025-05-31 08:58:43.000000',_binary '','2025-05-31 08:58:43.000000','He asked me where I _____ from.','Reported question: past simple.'),(59,'2025-05-31 08:58:43.000000',_binary '','2025-05-31 08:58:43.000000','The homework must _____ by tomorrow.','Passive voice: “be + past participle.”'),(60,'2025-05-31 08:58:43.000000',_binary '','2025-05-31 08:58:43.000000','She has been working here _____ five years.','Present perfect continuous + “for.”'),(61,'2025-05-31 08:58:43.000000',_binary '','2025-05-31 08:58:43.000000','I’m looking forward to _____ you soon.','Use gerund after “look forward to.”'),(62,'2025-0