e water crisis?','The passage lists several solutions including rainwater harvesting, desalination, and agricultural techniques, but not mass migration.'),(180,'2025-05-31 09:45:46.000000',_binary '','2025-05-31 09:45:46.000000','What causes ocean acidification according to the marine biologist?','The marine biologist states that \"As the ocean absorbs carbon dioxide from the atmosphere, it forms carbonic acid, gradually lowering the ocean\'s pH.\"'),(181,'2025-05-31 09:45:46.000000',_binary '','2025-05-31 09:45:46.000000','By what percentage have ocean surface waters become more acidic since the Industrial Revolution?','According to the transcript, \"Since the Industrial Revolution, ocean surface waters have become about 30% more acidic.\"'),(182,'2025-05-31 09:45:46.000000',_binary '','2025-05-31 09:45:46.000000','What percentage of marine species depend on coral reefs according to the recording?','The marine biologist mentions that losing coral ecosystems would affect \"the approximately 25% of marine species that depend on reefs.\"'),(183,'2025-05-31 09:45:46.000000',_binary '','2025-05-31 09:45:46.000000','Which technology sends radio waves into the soil according to the recording?','The archaeologist explains that \"Ground-penetrating radar sends radio waves into the soil and measures their reflection to create images of buried structures.\"'),(184,'2025-05-31 09:45:46.000000',_binary '','2025-05-31 09:45:46.000000','How do archaeologists record artifacts during excavation according to the recording?','The recording states that excavation is \"conducted methodically in a grid system, with each artifact\'s precise location recorded in three dimensions.\"'),(185,'2025-05-31 09:45:46.000000',_binary '','2025-05-31 09:45:46.000000','What dating technique measures radioactive isotopes according to the archaeologist?','The archaeologist mentions that \"radiocarbon dating can determine an organic object\'s age by measuring remaining amounts of the radioactive i