 over the past decade?','Maria states \"Over the past decade, I have traveled to more than thirty countries,\" using present perfect tense to describe her experiences up to the present moment.'),(261,'2025-06-03 22:34:50.996961',_binary '','2025-06-03 22:34:50.996976','What has forced families in Bangladesh to abandon their homes?','The speaker explains \"Rising sea levels have forced entire families to abandon their ancestral homes,\" using present perfect tense to describe the ongoing impact of climate change.'),(262,'2025-06-03 22:35:20.817039',_binary '','2025-06-03 22:35:20.817058','What did Maria witness in Norway?','Maria mentions \"In Norway, I witnessed cities that run entirely on renewable energy,\" using simple present tense to describe the current state of these cities.'),(263,'2025-06-03 22:35:52.677963',_binary '','2025-06-03 22:35:52.677972','According to Maria, what do we need to implement solutions on a larger scale?','She states \"we need political will, financial investment, and global cooperation to implement them on a larger scale,\" using simple present tense to express current necessity.'),(264,'2025-06-03 22:36:22.797287',_binary '','2025-06-03 22:36:22.797305','What does Maria say about the timing of action on climate change?','Maria emphasizes \"We must act with the knowledge we have right now,\" using modal verb \"must\" to express urgent necessity in the present.'),(265,'2025-06-03 23:13:08.442554',_binary '','2025-06-03 23:13:08.442575','According to Dr. Chen, what has transformed faster than most experts predicted?','Dr. Chen states \"Artificial intelligence has transformed from science fiction into everyday reality faster than most experts predicted,\" using present perfect tense to describe the rapid development.'),(266,'2025-06-03 23:13:42.184601',_binary '','2025-06-03 23:13:42.184613','What does Dr. Chen believe about the next breakthrough in AI?','He states \"The next breakthrough will likely come from combining different types of artificial intelligence,\" using future tense with modal verb \"will\" to express prediction.'),(267,'2025-06-03 23:14:10.018985',_binary '','2025-06-03 23:14:10.018996','In which timeframe does Dr. Chen predict AI will revolutionize personalized medicine?','Dr. Chen specifically mentions \"In the next five years, I predict that AI will revolutionize personalized medicine,\" using simple future tense for prediction.'),(268,'2025-06-03 23:14:34.632494',_binary '','2025-06-03 23:14:34.632506','What do current AI systems lack according to the lecture?','He explains that current systems \"lack general intelligence\" and \"cannot transfer knowledge from one domain to another,\" using simple present tense to describe current limitations.'),(269,'2025-06-03 23:15:02.834816',_binary '','2025-06-03 23:15:02.834849','What does Dr. Chen say is key to successful AI development?','He concludes \"The key to successful AI development lies in interdisciplinary collaboration,\" using simple present tense to state his opinion.'),(270,'2025-06-03 23:19:56.645430',_binary '','2025-06-03 23:19:56.645464','How long ago did Rebecca Martinez start her career?','She mentions \"When I started my career twenty-five years ago,\" using simple past tense to reference a specific time in the past.'),(271,'2025-06-03 23:20:25.674689',_binary '','2025-06-03 23:20:25.674702','By what average percentage have companies with strong ESG practices outperformed competitors?','Martinez states \"Companies with strong environmental, social, and governance practices have outperformed their competitors by an average of 15%,\" using present perfect tense to describe performance over time.'),(272,'2025-06-03 23:20:49.796967',_binary '','2025-06-03 23:20:49.796978','When did her company implement their sustainability program?','She clearly states \"Five years ago, we implemented a comprehensive sustainability program,\" using simple past tense with a specific time reference.'),(273,'2025-06-03 23:21:16.683927',_binary '','2025-06-03 23:21:16.683937','What does Martinez call the leadership approach where companies leave the world better than they found it?','She introduces the concept saying \"I believe businesses must embrace what I call \'regenerative leadership,\'\" using present tense to define her term.'),(274,'2025-06-03 23:21:39.751892',_binary '','2025-06-03 23:21:39.751901','What has her company\'s sustainability program achieved according to the speech?','She explains the program \"has saved us millions of dollars in operational costs while improving our brand reputation and employee satisfaction,\" using present perfect tense to describe cumulative results.'),(275,'2025-06-03 23:24:37.980979',_binary '','2025-06-03 23:24:37.981031','How long has Dr. Thompson been studying climate patterns and adaptation?','Dr. Thompson introduces herself saying \"I have been studying climate patterns and adaptation mechanisms for the past fifteen years,\" using present perfect continuous tense.'),(276,'2025-06-03 23:25:04.897476',_binary '','2025-06-03 23:25:04.897489','According to the economic analysis, how much money does every dollar spent on climate adaptation save?','She states \"Economic analyses show that every dollar spent on climate adaptation saves between four and seven dollars in future damage costs,\" using simple present tense for factual information.'),(277,'2025-06-03 23:25:32.356872',_binary '','2025-06-03 23:25:32.356883','By how much have precision farming techniques increased crop yields?','Dr. Thompson mentions \"These innovations have increased crop yields by up to 30%,\" using present perfect tense to describe achieved results.'),(278,'2025-06-03 23:25:56.047016',_binary '','2025-06-03 23:25:56.047030','What is the approximate cost of mangrove restoration per hectare in Vietnam?','She provides specific cost data: \"A mangrove restoration project in Vietnam costs approximately $1,000 per hectare,\" using simple present tense for current pricing.'),(279,'2025-06-03 23:26:22.395365',_binary '','2025-06-03 23:26:22.395377','According to Dr. Thompson, how much time do we have to implement large-scale adaptation measures?','She warns \"We have perhaps ten to fifteen years to implement large-scale adaptation measures,\" using simple present tense to express urgency about the timeline.'),(280,'2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000','What is the primary purpose of skimming according to the passage?','The passage clearly states that \"skimming involves quickly reading through a text to get the general idea or gist of the content.\"'),(281,'2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000','When scanning a text, readers should focus on:','The passage explains that scanning is \"a more targeted approach where you look for specific information within a text.\"'),(282,'2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000','Which elements should readers focus on when skimming?','The passage specifically mentions these elements as what readers typically focus on when skimming.'),(283,'2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000','According to the passage, metacognitive strategies include:','The passage lists these as examples of metacognitive strategies that help readers become more engaged.'),(284,'2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000','The main benefit of combining skimming and scanning with other strategies is:','The passage states that these strategies \"help readers become more engaged and purposeful in their approach to reading.\"'),(285,'2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000','What distinguishes active reading from traditional reading?','The passage explains that active reading \"involves constant dialogue between the reader and the material,\" unlike traditional one-way reading.'),(286,'2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000','In the SQ3R method, what does the first \'R\' represent?','The passage lists the SQ3R method as \"Survey, Question, Read, Recite, and Review,\" so the first R is \"Read.\"'),(287,'2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000','According to the passage, annotation helps with:','The passage states that annotation \"enhances memory retention and creates a personalized study guide.\"'),(288,'2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000','During the Question phase of SQ3R, readers should:','The passage clearly states that \"The Question phase involves formulating specific questions about the content before reading.\"'),(289,'2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000','Research shows that active reading strategies result in:','The passage mentions that \"students who employ active reading strategies demonstrate significantly better comprehension and retention.\"'),(290,'2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000','According to the passage, reading challenges should be viewed as:','The passage explicitly states that challenges \"are opportunities for growth and skill development.\"'),(291,'2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000','The best approach to expanding vocabulary while reading is:','The passage recommends \"contextual learning, where readers use surrounding clues to infer word meanings.\"'),(292,'2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000','When should readers research unfamiliar words according to the passage?','The passage suggests noting unfamiliar words and researching them \"after completing the reading session to avoid disrupting their flow.\"'),(293,'2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000','The Pomodoro Technique involves:','The passage clearly describes the Pomodoro Technique as \"25-minute focused reading sessions followed by 5-minute breaks.\"'),(294,'2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000','To overcome concentration difficulties, readers should:','The passage states that \"successful readers create optimal reading environments by eliminating distractions.\"'),(295,'2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000','What is described as the most valuable skill for vocabulary development?','The passage states that \"the ability to determine the meaning of unfamiliar words through context clues is perhaps the most valuable skill for vocabulary development.\"'),(296,'2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000','In the example \"The arborist, a specialist in tree care, examined the diseased oak,\" what type of context clue is used?','The passage identifies this as an example of definition clues, where \"the author directly provides the meaning of a word within the same sentence.\"'),(297,'2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000','Which type of context clue is demonstrated in the nocturnal animals example?','The passage uses this as an example of \"example clues [that] provide specific instances or illustrations that clarify a word\'s meaning.\"'),(298,'2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000','According to the passage, words learned through context are better retained because they:','The passage explains that context-learned words \"are better retained because they are associated with meaningful situations and connected to broader knowledge networks.\"'),(299,'2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000','Inference clues require readers to:','The passage states that \"inference clues require more sophisticated thinking, as readers must combine multiple pieces of information from the surrounding text.\"'),(300,'2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000','What is morphology according to the passage?','The passage clearly defines morphology as \"the study of word structure.\"'),(301,'2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000','The prefix \"re-\" typically suggests:','The passage states that \"\'re-\' suggests repetition or doing something again.\"'),(302,'2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000','The Latin root \"spect\" means:','The passage explicitly states that \"The Latin root \'spect,\' meaning \'to see.\'\"'),(303,'2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000','What does the suffix \"-tion\" typically do to words?','The passage explains that \"The suffix \'-tion\' typically transforms verbs into nouns.\"'),(304,'2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000','Understanding morphological patterns helps readers by:','The passage states that understanding these patterns allows readers to \"decode unfamiliar words by analyzing their component parts.\"'),(305,'2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000','According to the passage, why should readers diversify their reading materials?','The passage states that diversifying reading \"exponentially enhances vocabulary development by exposing readers to specialized terminology, different writing styles, and unique linguistic patterns.\"'),(306,'2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000','Scientific texts are characterized by:','The passage describes scientific texts as introducing \"precise technical terminology and formal academic language.\"'),(307,'2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000','The difference between \"house\" and \"home\" illustrates:','The passage uses this example to show how \"house\" simply denotes while \"home\" connotes emotional connection, illustrating denotative vs. connotative meaning.'),(308,'2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000','News articles and journalistic writing help readers with:','The passage states that news articles \"provide contemporary vocabulary related to current events, politics, economics, and social issues\" and introduce \"terminology relevant to civic engagement.\"'),(309,'2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000','Literary fiction contributes to vocabulary development by:','The passage describes literary fiction as offering \"rich descriptive language, nuanced emotional vocabulary, and creative word usage.\"'),(310,'2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000','What are the three primary purposes for writing mentioned in the passage?','The passage explicitly states \"The three primary purposes for writing are to inform, to persuade, and to entertain.\"'),(311,'2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000','According to the passage, even factual presentations can contain bias through:','The passage specifically mentions these three ways that bias can appear in factual presentations.'),(312,'2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000','Persuasive writing can be challenging to identify because:','The passage states that \"skilled writers may disguise persuasive intent within seemingly objective presentations.\"'),(313,'2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000','To evaluate bias effectively, critical readers should consider:','The passage lists these four factors as important considerations for evaluating bias.'),(314,'2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000','The analytical approach to reading transforms passive reading into:','The passage concludes that \"This analytical approach transforms passive reading into active intellectual engagement.\"'),(315,'2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000','According to the passage, strong arguments must contain:','The passage explicitly states that \"Strong arguments contain clear claims supported by relevant, credible evidence and logical reasoning.\"'),(316,'2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000','What is a limitation of anecdotal evidence mentioned in the passage?','The passage states that anecdotal evidence \"lacks the generalizability of larger studies.\"'),(317,'2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000','A straw man fallacy involves:','The passage defines straw man fallacies as those that \"misrepresent opposing viewpoints to make them easier to attack.\"'),(318,'2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000','What characterizes an ad hominem attack?','The passage defines ad hominem attacks as those that \"target the person making an argument rather than addressing the argument itself.\"'),(319,'2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000','Critical readers must distinguish between:','The passage states that critical readers \"must distinguish between appropriate emotional appeals and manipulative tactics designed to bypass rational thinking.\"'),(320,'2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000','What distinguishes synthesis from simple summarization?','The passage states that synthesis \"requires active mental processing that goes far beyond simple summarization or repetition of source material.\"'),(321,'2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000','When multiple credible sources agree, readers can:','The passage indicates that \"When multiple credible sources agree on fundamental facts or conclusions, readers can feel more confident about the reliability of that information.\"'),(322,'2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000','According to the passage, areas of disagreement between sources:','The passage states that disagreements \"highlight ongoing debates, evolving understanding, or the complexity of issues that resist simple answers.\"'),(323,'2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000','Which type of source generally carries more weight according to the passage?','The passage states that \"Academic peer-reviewed journals generally carry more weight than personal blogs or opinion pieces.\"'),(324,'2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 02:52:55.000000','Successful synthesis transforms readers into:','The passage describes how synthesis \"transforms readers from passive consumers of information into active knowledge creators who can contribute meaningfully to academic and professional discussions.\"'),(325,'2025-06-11 03:13:08.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 03:13:08.000000','According to Ms. Johnson, what must students do by Friday?','Ms. Johnson clearly states \"We must submit our permission forms by Friday,\" using the modal verb \"must\" to express obligation.'),(326,'2025-06-11 03:13:08.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 03:13:08.000000','What does the modal verb \"might\" express in \"You might also want to bring a water bottle\"?','\"Might\" is used here to express a gentle suggestion or possibility, not a strong requirement.'),(327,'2025-06-11 03:13:08.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 03:13:08.000000','In the sentence \"Students who don\'t have their forms cannot join the trip,\" what does \"cannot\" express?','\"Cannot\" here expresses prohibition - students are not allowed/unable to join without forms.'),(328,'2025-06-11 03:13:08.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 03:13:08.000000','When Sarah asks \"Could we stay longer...?\", what is she doing?','\"Could\" is used to make a polite request or ask for permission in a formal way.'),(329,'2025-06-11 03:13:08.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 03:13:08.000000','What does \"should\" express in \"We should respect the museum rules\"?','\"Should\" expresses advice or moral obligation - what is the right thing to do.'),(330,'2025-06-11 03:13:08.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 03:13:08.000000','What does Lisa mean when she says \"You must dress professionally\"?','\"Must\" expresses strong obligation or necessity - professional dress is essential for the interview.'),(331,'2025-06-11 03:13:08.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 03:13:08.000000','In \"The interviewer could ask you about your previous experience,\" what does \"could\" express?','\"Could\" here expresses possibility - it\'s something that might happen during the interview.'),(332,'2025-06-11 03:13:08.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 03:13:08.000000','What type of advice does \"should\" give in \"You should prepare examples\"?','\"Should\" is used to give advice or recommendations about what would be wise to do.'),(333,'2025-06-11 03:13:08.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 03:13:08.000000','Why does Lisa say \"You must not ask about salary\"?','\"Must not\" expresses strong prohibition - it\'s something that should definitely not be done.'),(334,'2025-06-11 03:13:08.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 03:13:08.000000','In \"With proper preparation, you could get this job!\", what does \"could\" express?','\"Could\" here expresses future possibility or potential - what might happen if he prepares well.'),(335,'2025-06-11 03:13:08.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 03:13:08.000000','In \"I could have a fresh start there,\" what does \"could\" express?','\"Could\" expresses the possibility or potential for a fresh start if she moves to Seattle.'),(336,'2025-06-11 03:13:08.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 03:13:08.000000','What does \"must\" express in \"You must consider both the career opportunities and your personal happiness\"?','\"Must\" here expresses strong advice or necessity - it\'s essential that she considers both aspects.'),(337,'2025-06-11 03:13:08.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 03:13:08.000000','In \"I can\'t make such an important decision,\" what does \"can\'t\" express?','\"Can\'t\" expresses that she feels unable/it\'s impossible to make the decision without more thought.'),(338,'2025-06-11 03:13:08.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 03:13:08.000000','What does \"might\" express in \"This opportunity might not come again\"?','\"Might not\" expresses possibility/uncertainty - there\'s a chance this opportunity won\'t happen again.'),(339,'2025-06-11 03:13:08.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 03:13:08.000000','In \"I will call them tomorrow,\" what does \"will\" express?','\"Will\" expresses her future intention or firm decision to call them tomorrow.'),(340,'2025-06-11 03:13:08.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 03:13:08.000000','\"If I wake up late tomorrow, I will use the express train\" is an example of:','This uses if + present simple, will + base verb structure, expressing a real future possibility.'),(341,'2025-06-11 03:13:08.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 03:13:08.000000','\"If I had studied computer science instead of literature, I would be working in a tech company now\" represents:','This mixes Type 3 (if + past perfect) with Type 2 result (would + be + -ing), showing past condition affecting present result.'),(342,'2025-06-11 03:13:08.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 03:13:08.000000','\"If I were more skilled with technology, I would probably earn a higher salary\" is:','Uses if + past subjunctive (were), would + base verb, expressing hypothetical present situation.'),(343,'2025-06-11 03:13:08.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 03:13:08.000000','\"If you start learning programming now, you will have better job opportunities\" shows:','Type 1 conditional structure (if + present, will + base verb) expressing a real, achievable future possibility.'),(344,'2025-06-11 03:13:08.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 03:13:08.000000','\"If I had backed up my files regularly, I wouldn\'t have lost all my work\" expresses:','Type 3 conditional (if + past perfect, would + have + past participle) expressing regret about past events.'),(345,'2025-06-11 03:13:08.000000',_binary '','2025-06-11 03:13:08.000000','\"If you exercise regularly, you will feel more energetic\" is what type of conditional?','Uses if + present simple, will + base verb structure, expressing a real future result of regular exercise.'),(346,'2025-06