INSERT INTO `submit_test_writing` (`id`, `created_at`, `status`, `updated_at`, `comment`, `content`, `score`, `submit_test_id`, `testwriting_id`) VALUES (1,'2025-06-03 21:37:27.029160',_binary '','2025-06-03 21:37:56.198669','Error processing writing sample: Error checking text with LanguageTool: I/O error on POST request for \"http://localhost:8081/v2/check\": Connection refused','I usually wake up at 6:30 AM every morning and start my day with a cup of coffee. I always check my emails and read the news while having breakfast. After that, I take the bus to work because it is more convenient than driving. I work as a marketing manager, and my office hours are from 9:00 AM to 5:30 PM. During lunch break, I often eat with my colleagues at a nearby restaurant.\nHowever, this week I am doing things quite differently. I am currently working from home because my office is being renovated. I am also taking an online course in digital marketing, so I am spending extra hours studying in the evenings. My schedule is more flexible now, and I am enjoying the change of pace. I am waking up a bit later than usual and having more time for breakfast.\nIn the afternoons, I am attending virtual meetings with clients and am learning new software programs. I am also cooking more meals at home instead of eating out. This temporary change is teaching me to be more organized with my time, and I am discovering that I am actually more productive when working from home.',0,5,17),(2,'2025-06-03 21:37:42.961287',_binary '','2025-06-03 21:37:56.223956','Error processing writing sample: Error checking text with LanguageTool: I/O error on POST request for \"http://localhost:8081/v2/check\": Connection refused','\nI have experienced many significant changes in my life that have shaped who I am today. Five years ago, I have moved to a new city to pursue my university education, and this decision has completely transformed my perspective on life. I have met people from different cultural backgrounds and have learned to be more open-minded and tolerant.\nDuring my university years, I have joined several student organizations and have developed strong leadership skills. I have also traveled to three different countries, which has broadened my understanding of the world. Recently, I have completed my degree in business administration and have started my first professional job. These experiences have taught me the importance of perseverance and hard work.\nAll these life changes now influence how I approach daily challenges. I believe that every experience teaches us valuable lessons, and I always try to learn something new from difficult situations. I am more confident in my abilities now because I have overcome many obstacles in the past. My travels have made me appreciate different cultures, so I enjoy working in diverse environments. The leadership experience I have gained helps me communicate effectively with my colleagues and manage projects successfully.',0,5,18),(3,'2025-06-03 21:37:50.107857',_binary '','2025-06-03 21:37:56.249406','Error processing writing sample: Error checking text with LanguageTool: I/O error on POST request for \"http://localhost:8081/v2/check\": Connection refused','I am currently working on several exciting projects that are helping me grow professionally. I am developing a new marketing campaign for our company\'s latest product launch, and I am collaborating with a team of creative designers. We are also conducting market research to better understand our target audience.\nIn my personal life, I am learning Spanish through online classes and am practicing with native speakers twice a week. I am also training for a half-marathon that will take place next month, so I am running five kilometers every other day.\nRecently, I have completed a professional certification in project management, which has already improved my job performance. I have also started volunteering at a local animal shelter, and this experience has been incredibly rewarding. I have made new friends through this volunteer work and have learned about animal care.\nLooking ahead, I believe that continuous learning is essential for career success. I want to become a marketing director within the next five years, and I know that I need to develop my skills further. I am planning to pursue a master\'s degree in marketing next year, and I am already researching different universities and programs.',0,5,19),(4,'2025-06-03 21:40:42.021928',_binary '','2025-06-03 21:41:29.359875','The composition effectively describes the daily routine and the current changes with clarity and relevance. The lexical diversity and vocabulary usage are strong, but incorporating more complex sentence structures and deeper insights could further enhance the writing quality.','I usually wake up at 6:30 AM every morning and start my day with a cup of coffee. I always check my emails and read the news while having breakfast. After that, I take the bus to work because it is more convenient than driving. I work as a marketing manager, and my office hours are from 9:00 AM to 5:30 PM. During lunch break, I often eat with my colleagues at a nearby restaurant.\nHowever, this week I am doing things quite differently. I am currently working from home because my office is being renovated. I am also taking an online course in digital marketing, so I am spending extra hours studying in the evenings. My schedule is more flexible now, and I am enjoying the change of pace. I am waking up a bit later than usual and having more time for breakfast.\nIn the afternoons, I am attending virtual meetings with clients and am learning new software programs. I am also cooking more meals at home instead of eating out. This temporary change is teaching me to be more organized with my time, and I am discovering that I am actually more productive when working from home.',28,6,17),(5,'2025-06-03 21:40:48.245708',_binary '','2025-06-03 21:41:36.294991','This essay demonstrates a strong command of English with excellent vocabulary and grammar. The topic is well-developed with relevant examples, but readability could be improved by adjusting sentence structure. The conclusion could be more impactful.','I have experienced many significant changes in my life that have shaped who I am today. Five years ago, I have moved to a new city to pursue my university education, and this decision has completely transformed my perspective on life. I have met people from different cultural backgrounds and have learned to be more open-minded and tolerant.\nDuring my university years, I have joined several student organizations and have developed strong leadership skills. I have also traveled to three different countries, which has broadened my understanding of the world. Recently, I have completed my degree in business administration and have started my first professional job. These experiences have taught me the importance of perseverance and hard work.\nAll these life changes now influence how I approach daily challenges. I believe that every experience teaches us valuable lessons, and I always try to learn something new from difficult situations. I am more confident in my abilities now because I have overcome many obstacles in the past. My travels have made me appreciate different cultures, so I enjoy working in diverse environments. The leadership experience I have gained helps me communicate effectively with my colleagues and manage projects successfully.',28,6,18),(6,'2025-06-03 21:41:19.804541',_binary '','2025-06-03 21:41:44.746223','The text demonstrates a solid command of vocabulary and maintains strong relevance to the topic. The organization is clear, with well-developed ideas and supporting examples. Minor improvements in grammar and sentence structure could further enhance the overall quality. The readability score suggests some complexity, but the lexical diversity is commendable.','I am currently working on several exciting projects that are helping me grow professionally. I am developing a new marketing campaign for our company\'s latest product launch, and I am collaborating with a team of creative designers. We are also conducting market research to better understand our target audience.\nIn my personal life, I am learning Spanish through online classes and am practicing with native speakers twice a week. I am also training for a half-marathon that will take place next month, so I am running five kilometers every other day.\nRecently, I have completed a professional certification in project management, which has already improved my job performance. I have also started volunteering at a local animal shelter, and this experience has been incredibly rewarding. I have made new friends through this volunteer work and have learned about animal care.\nLooking ahead, I believe that continuous learning is essential for career success. I want to become a marketing director within the next five years, and I know that I need to develop my skills further. I am planning to pursue a master\'s degree in marketing next year, and I am already researching different universities and programs.',29,6,19),(7,'2025-06-11 21:56:05.630601',_binary '','2025-06-11 21:56:49.033756','The text demonstrates a solid grasp of the topic with clear arguments and good vocabulary use. However, it could benefit from more detailed examples, improved punctuation, and a stronger conclusion to enhance overall effectiveness.','There are different opinions about when children should start learning foreign languages. Some people believe young children should begin learning languages early because their brains absorb new information quickly and they can develop better pronunciation. They argue that children who start young will become more fluent speakers. However, others think children should focus on mastering their native language first before learning foreign languages, as it might confuse them or slow down their development. In my opinion, starting foreign language learning at a young age is beneficial because children are naturally curious and learn through play, making language acquisition more enjoyable and effective for them.',6,11,10),(8,'2025-06-11 21:56:27.039441',_binary '','2025-06-11 21:56:43.935308','This is a well-written response with strong vocabulary, grammar, and logical flow. It thoroughly addresses the topic and proposes viable solutions. Minor improvements in word choice and sentence variety could elevate it further.','Traffic congestion in cities is caused by several factors including the increasing number of private cars, inadequate public transportation systems, and poor urban planning that forces people to travel long distances for work. Many people prefer driving their own cars because public transport is often unreliable or uncomfortable. To solve this problem, cities should invest in better public transportation like buses and trains, encourage carpooling and cycling by building bike lanes, and implement congestion charges for driving in busy areas. Additionally, promoting remote work and flexible working hours can help reduce the number of people traveling during peak times, making traffic flow more smoothly throughout the day.',6,11,11);
