INSERT INTO `writing` (`id`, `created_at`, `status`, `updated_at`, `description`, `image`, `title`, `views`, `file`, `paragraph`, `topic`, `route_node_id`, `preparation_id`) VALUES (1,'2025-05-17 10:23:41.138163',_binary '','2025-06-03 17:22:01.905438','In this lesson, you will write about recycle','http://138.2.91.94:9000/h2t-english/writing/-1-3d4ab42f-d0f2-4d9c-9cf3-887fe8efef33','Recycle',0,'http://138.2.91.94:9000/h2t-english/writing/1-12834d5a-71af-4cfd-875c-234b0da50b76','Recycling in my house separating paper, plastic, and glass. We labeled bins and compost food waste. This small effort helps protect our environment for future generations.','Recycle in your house',NULL,3),(2,'2025-06-02 15:41:39.331196',_binary '','2025-06-11 23:09:22.392471','This lesson helps students improve their English writing skills by focusing on local environmental pollution issues. Students will learn relevant vocabulary, practice sentence structure, and write a short paragraph.','http://138.2.91.94:9000/h2t-english/writing/2-b87dc80b-0f8d-4ce2-a875-df3adf636226','Local Environmental Pollution',5,'http://138.2.91.94:9000/h2t-english/writing/2-e66b2f1b-249b-4163-8e34-58344f18a591','Pollution is a serious in many cities. Factories release harmful into the air, and people often throw on the streets. To reduce pollution, we should more and use energy sources like solar power.','How Can Students Help Reduce Pollution in Their Community?',NULL,15),(3,'2025-06-02 15:49:34.505168',_binary '','2025-06-15 18:07:48.764597','This lesson helps students learn how to confidently introduce themselves in English, covering basic personal information, hobbies, and daily routines.','http://138.2.91.94:9000/h2t-english/writing/3-18f62a83-3a74-4711-9ed7-fb016f35319a','Introducing Yourself',2,'http://138.2.91.94:9000/h2t-english/writing/3-121fd707-1ad5-4801-9dd5-8e113aeeb46a','My is David. I am 30 years , and I come Canada. I work as a in the hospitalhospital. In my free time, I like  books and watching movies.','Introduce yourself in front of the crowd',NULL,16),(4,'2025-06-02 15:56:59.494047',_binary '','2025-06-03 17:14:16.723021','This lesson teaches students how to describe their daily work routines in English, using proper time expressions and action verbs.','http://138.2.91.94:9000/h2t-english/writing/4-37a88680-039b-46d2-84cc-4b36a6c52ecb','Daily Work Schedule',0,'http://138.2.91.94:9000/h2t-english/writing/4-fb8782f6-60ad-47bd-81ad-e9ed58278383','I up at 6:30 AM every weekday. First, I breakfast and ready for work. My work at 8:00 AM. I usually my most important tasks in the morning.','Describe Your Ideal Workday',NULL,17),(5,'2025-06-15 17:44:28.342837',_binary '','2025-06-15 17:48:53.203138','Students will develop persuasive writing skills by creating compelling essays about environmental pollution issues in their local community. This lesson combines environmental awareness with advanced writing techniques to help students craft impactful argumentative pieces.','http://138.2.91.94:9000/h2t-english/writing/-1-d71bb5b9-1613-4dfd-85af-b79d84d1be25','Voices for Change: Writing About Local Environmental Pollution',0,'http://138.2.91.94:9000/h2t-english/writing/-1-9274457a-533e-44fe-b883-988b7e3e94cd','Air pollution in urban areas has become a (1)_______ concern for public health officials worldwide. The primary (2)_______ of this pollution include vehicle emissions, industrial waste, and construction activities. When harmful (3)_______ are released into the atmosphere, they can cause serious respiratory problems, especially for children and elderly people. Many cities are now implementing (4)_______ transportation systems and promoting renewable energy sources to (5)_______ the impact of pollution on their communities. Citizens can also contribute by using public transportation, recycling waste, and supporting (6)_______ businesses that prioritize environmental protection.','Plastic Waste Management in Your Neighborhood',NULL,64),(6,'2025-06-15 17:56:15.860706',_binary '','2025-06-15 17:57:22.018378','Students will master narrative writing techniques by creating engaging stories about fitness challenges, focusing on character development, conflict resolution, and descriptive language. This lesson combines personal experience writing with creative storytelling to develop compelling narratives about perseverance and personal growth.','http://138.2.91.94:9000/h2t-english/writing/-1-9ab07373-5013-43a9-9563-184ddb148dc0','30-Day Fitness Challenge: Who Quit First? - Writing Personal Narratives and Character Development',0,'http://138.2.91.94:9000/h2t-english/writing/-1-b040367a-4a37-4366-8c84-fe29649c3fbb','The 30-day fitness challenge began with great enthusiasm from all participants. Sarah was the most dedicated member, never missing a single workout session. However, by day 10, Mark started making excuses about why he couldn\'t attend the morning exercises. The group tried to encourage him to continue, but his motivation was clearly decreasing. When the challenge reached its halfway point, two people had already dropped out, leaving only three determined individuals to complete the remaining days. Despite the setbacks, the remaining participants felt more determined than ever to reach their .','Write a 100-word narrative paragraph describing a specific moment when you wanted to quit during a personal challenge (fitness, academic, hobby, etc.)',NULL,65),(7,'2025-06-15 18:01:48.438939',_binary '','2025-06-15 18:03:39.731800','Students will develop comedic writing skills by creating entertaining stories about technology-related disagreements in relationships. This lesson focuses on dialogue writing, character voice, and humor techniques in everyday domestic scenarios.','http://138.2.91.94:9000/h2t-english/writing/-1-44926b73-42ba-42dc-b002-b96bc2c84f47','His Chrome Tabs vs Her Safari: The Browser War at Home - Writing Humorous Relationship Conflicts',0,'http://138.2.91.94:9000/h2t-english/writing/-1-1b040b49-5908-4003-8138-c9731470d710','\"I can\'t believe you use Internet Explorer,\" Sarah said, staring at her boyfriend\'s laptop screen in . \"It\'s 2025, not 2005!\"\nDavid shrugged and clicked refresh for the third time. \"It just fine for me. Besides, all my passwords are saved here.\"\n\"That\'s exactly the !\" Sarah exclaimed, switching to her MacBook with lightning-fast Safari loading times.','The Day Our WiFi Died and We Blamed Each Other\'s Devices',NULL,66),(8,'2025-06-15 18:06:15.431570',_binary '','2025-06-15 18:07:11.420312','Students will master humorous conflict writing by exploring the universal household battle over thermostat control. This lesson develops skills in character perspective, escalating tension, and comedic timing through relatable domestic scenarios.','http://138.2.91.94:9000/h2t-english/writing/-1-b1a64fe1-0417-4c42-9152-8c8024c6c4fd','The Thermostat Conflict: Summer in Winter - Writing Domestic Temperature Wars',0,'http://138.2.91.94:9000/h2t-english/writing/-1-d2780c14-2b27-4139-aa3e-dabf8edab661','Mark walked into the living room and immediately felt like he was entering a sauna. His wife had clearly been at the thermostat again, setting it to her preferred temperature of 78 degrees. He quietly adjusted it back down to 72 degrees, hoping she wouldn\'t notice. Within minutes, Sarah appeared wearing a thick sweater and gave him her famous disapproving .','The Day We Discovered Our Perfect Room Temperature',NULL,67),(9,'2025-06-15 18:27:31.900565',_binary '','2025-06-15 18:30:45.951728','Students will develop narrative writing skills by creating engaging stories about unexpected travel accommodation challenges. This lesson focuses on dialogue, character reactions, and problem-solving through descriptive storytelling.','http://138.2.91.94:9000/h2t-english/writing/-1-66c5b9be-9e97-442f-93b2-01fa480e7fc2','The Hostel Surprise: Mixed Dormitory Dilemma - Writing Unexpected Travel Situations',0,'http://138.2.91.94:9000/h2t-english/writing/-1-08af619d-bb4e-470b-862f-97cf454eeea1','When Jake opened the dormitory door, he was shocked to discover his was not what he had expected. The booking website had clearly stated \"mixed accommodation,\" but he had assumed this meant people from different . Standing in the doorway with his heavy backpack, he realized he would need to quickly to this unexpected situation.','The Day My Travel Plans Went Completely Wrong',NULL,68),(10,'2025-06-15 18:33:59.772337',_binary '','2025-06-15 18:35:57.300631','Students will master comedic dialogue writing by exploring the passionate debate between sweet and savory breakfast lovers. This lesson develops skills in character voice, persuasive arguments, and humorous food-related conflicts.','http://138.2.91.94:9000/h2t-english/writing/-1-db43e016-ee6e-42ee-9a15-6ecbb09596de','The Great Brunch Debate: Sweet vs. Savory - Writing Food Preference Conflicts',0,'http://138.2.91.94:9000/h2t-english/writing/-1-01cfdd6a-1988-434b-a6d3-136de3c5f263','I can\'t believe you ordered pancakes again,\" Sarah said, watching her friend pour over the stack of fluffy breakfast treats. \"Don\'t you ever crave something like eggs or bacon?\"\nLisa shrugged and took a large bite of her sweet breakfast. \"Life\'s too short to skip for breakfast. Besides, these pancakes are basically happiness on a plate.','The Most Unusual Breakfast Combination I Ever Tried',NULL,69),(11,'2025-06-15 18:37:45.265289',_binary '','2025-06-15 18:39:18.823154','Students will develop negotiation dialogue writing by exploring the classic entertainment conflict between action and romance movie preferences. This lesson focuses on compromise, persuasive language, and character-driven conflict resolution.','http://138.2.91.94:9000/h2t-english/writing/-1-23e38ba6-5d67-4414-92c1-d90e88fd51a5','Movie Night Compromise: Action vs. Romance - Finding Common Ground in Film Choices',0,'http://138.2.91.94:9000/h2t-english/writing/-1-787b5ee0-5490-4320-9b54-9e0ad603f64c','We always watch action movies,\" Lisa complained, scrolling through the streaming service options. \"Can\'t we pick something with actual development for once?\"\nMike sighed and pointed at the screen. \"But look at this one - explosions, car chases, and the main character saves the world! That\'s way more than watching people talk about their feelings for two hours.\"\n\"Fine,\" Lisa said with a smile, \"let\'s find something with both romance and scenes. Compromise time!','The Movie That Changed My Mind About a Genre I Used to Hate',NULL,70),(12,'2025-06-15 18:44:38.264991',_binary '','2025-06-15 18:46:07.134439','Students will master character contrast writing by exploring the clash between serious board game strategists and casual fun-loving players. This lesson develops skills in personality revelation through actions, escalating tension, and humor in competitive situations.','http://138.2.91.94:9000/h2t-english/writing/-1-c5848d53-5532-4941-b2b5-b0ad1c141164','Board Game Battle: Competitive vs. Casual Play - Different Gaming Approaches',0,'http://138.2.91.94:9000/h2t-english/writing/-1-d3c02e6f-b2e3-4d6a-9cc8-6f526e52b61c','When the board game came out, Jessica immediately began reading the carefully while Mark started rolling dice just to hear the sound. \"We need to understand the victory conditions,\" Jessica explained, but Mark was already arranging the game pieces by . By the end of the night, they realized that having different gaming actually made the experience more interesting for everyone.','The Game That Brought Out My Competitive Side',NULL,71),(13,'2025-06-15 18:48:19.118414',_binary '','2025-06-15 18:50:21.610908','Students will develop dynamic conflict writing by exploring the universal struggle for music control during road trips. This lesson focuses on character voice through music preferences, escalating musical warfare, and creative resolution techniques.','http://138.2.91.94:9000/h2t-english/writing/-1-ede21b73-e650-45b6-86f2-3cac449f82c5','The Music Road Trip: Who Controlled the Playlist? - Battling over Car Tunes',0,'http://138.2.91.94:9000/h2t-english/writing/-1-c806646a-2c1d-4709-9e85-88426fca8d09','As soon as Tom got in the driver\'s seat, he immediately connected his phone to the car\'s system and started playing heavy metal music. \"My car, my !\" he announced loudly over the guitar solo. His passengers groaned and began negotiating for more balanced choices for the long journey ahead.','The Song That Saved Our Road Trip',NULL,72),(14,'2025-06-15 18:52:43.592003',_binary '','2025-06-15 18:54:00.345139','Students will develop cross-cultural narrative writing by exploring the humorous and touching moments of language learning between friends. This lesson focuses on dialogue authenticity, cultural misunderstandings, and character growth through linguistic challenges.','http://138.2.91.94:9000/h2t-english/writing/-1-5f337086-e8df-4f37-a3b8-2e1f893e0fa8','Language Exchange: Teaching Each Other Native Tongues - A Cultural and Linguistic Exchange',0,'http://138.2.91.94:9000/h2t-english/writing/-1-5064c40d-1dc2-4511-8f4e-94f21c9d4444','When Sarah first started her language exchange with Chen, she was nervous about making while speaking Chinese. However, Chen was very and helped her practice pronunciation every day. After several weeks, Sarah\'s improved dramatically, and they became close friends through their shared learning experience.','The Day I Finally Understood My Foreign Friend\'s Joke',NULL,73),(15,'2025-06-15 18:56:09.865253',_binary '','2025-06-15 18:57:31.829926','Students will master comparative character writing by exploring the clash between organized planners and spontaneous shoppers in supermarket settings. This lesson develops skills in behavioral contrast, consumer psychology, and humorous domestic situations.','http://138.2.91.94:9000/h2t-english/writing/-1-27de2acb-3c2a-445e-82c2-a9a13b6dd0f0','Grocery Shopping Styles: List vs. Impulse - Contrasting Supermarket Strategies',0,'http://138.2.91.94:9000/h2t-english/writing/-1-00efa19f-e1fd-4bb2-bbd6-8dcf66662940','When Lisa and Tom entered the supermarket, Lisa immediately pulled out her carefully prepared shopping while Tom wandered toward the candy aisle. \"We need to stick to the budget,\" Lisa reminded him, but Tom was already adding chocolate bars to their . By the end of their shopping trip, they realized that combining planning with occasional purchases actually made the experience more enjoyable.','The Most Unnecessary Thing I Ever Bought at a Store',NULL,74);
